&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://www.jometer.com/v2/track?c=j9z3&amp;amp;a=2&quot; width=&quot;1&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW123259309 BCX8&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW123259309 BCX8&quot;&gt;We’re&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW123259309 BCX8&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;engineering the future of aerospace and defense. If you thrive on tackling complex challenges and delivering solutions where precision and reliability are non-negotiable, we want you on our team. Here, your&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW123259309 BCX8&quot;&gt;expertise&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW123259309 BCX8&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;powers mission-critical systems that safeguard lives, advance technology, and push the boundaries of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW123259309 BCX8&quot;&gt;what’s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW123259309 BCX8&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;possible. Join us and bring your skills to work where innovation meets impact.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;EOP SCXW123259309 BCX8&quot; data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:0}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Quest Defense Systems and Solutions is growing and looking for a Client Partner to lead and grow strategic accounts within the Aerospace &amp;amp; Defense sector, driving revenue, profitability, and long-term partnerships. This role is ideal for a consultative sales leader who understands engineering services and digital transformation and can translate customer needs into high-value solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll own the full account lifecycle—from relationship building and opportunity creation to deal closure and account expansion—while partnering with delivery and leadership teams to scale impact across complex A&amp;amp;D programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Cincinnati, OH (onsite/hybrid as applicable)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirement:&lt;/strong&gt; U.S. Citizenship required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and grow strategic aerospace &amp;amp; defense accounts ($8M+ revenue)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain executive-level client relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive full business development lifecycle (prospect → qualify → propose → close)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute account growth strategies (SWOT, whitespace, competitive positioning)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead solution-based selling across engineering and digital services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and drive cross-sell / up-sell opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with delivery teams to ensure successful execution and client satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead proposal development, pricing strategy, and contract negotiations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage forecasting, revenue targets, and profitability (P&amp;amp;L ownership)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expand accounts across new programs, geographies, and service lines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in account management, business development, or sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven success managing and growing large strategic accounts ($8M–$10M+)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Aerospace &amp;amp; Defense industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of engineering services and digital solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience selling into technical stakeholders and executive leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in complex

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://www.jometer.com/v2/track?c=j9z3&amp;amp;a=2&quot; width=&quot;1&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Immediately hiring engineers who want to contribute to mission-critical systems that demand precision, accountability, and technical excellence. Success here means solving real problems that keep complex systems moving forward.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Cybersecurity Compliance Engineer to support the implementation, maintenance, and validation of cybersecurity controls for engineering test equipment, systems, and operational technology (OT) environments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will work with engineering, production, procurement, and IT teams to ensure systems comply with regulatory, contractual, and enterprise cybersecurity requirements. You will implement technical security controls, assess system vulnerabilities, support Authority to Operate (ATO) activities, and help maintain secure, compliant production environments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is ideal for a cybersecurity professional with experience supporting regulated environments, systems administration, vulnerability management, and cybersecurity compliance frameworks such as NIST SP 800-171 and CMMC.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a 100% onsite position based in Tucson, Arizona, where you&#39;ll enjoy the collaboration of working alongside your team every day. With more than 310 days of sunshine each year, stunning mountain views, and a vibrant yet relaxed lifestyle, Tucson offers an exceptional place to build both your career and your life.&amp;nbsp; All candidates must be US Citizens due to the nature of the work.&amp;nbsp; Clearance or the ability to obtain a clearance is strongly preferred unless otherwise stated below. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and&amp;nbsp;maintain&amp;nbsp;cybersecurity controls for engineering test equipment, systems, and supporting infrastructure.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with cybersecurity frameworks and contractual requirements, including:&amp;nbsp;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NIST SP 800-171&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CMMC&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;DFARS 252.204-7012&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NIST SP 800-53 (as applicable)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NIST SP 800-82 for Operational Technology (OT) environments&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate cybersecurity and regulatory requirements into technical security controls and implementation plans.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Authority to Operate (ATO) activities by preparing and&amp;nbsp;maintaining&amp;nbsp;required cybersecurity artifacts and documentation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform system vulnerability assessments and remediation activities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain&amp;nbsp;accurate&amp;nbsp;asset inventories and configuration records&amp;nbsp;in accordance with&amp;nbsp;iRAMP&amp;nbsp;and organizational cybersecurity requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide&amp;nbsp;cybersecurity guidance to engineering teams supporting production and procurement of test equipment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install software packages, operating system updates, and security patches on engineering systems and test equipment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot engineering test equipment to ensure secure operation, connectivity, functionality, and compliance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Digital Technologies and infrastructure teams to integrate engineering systems into secure enterprise networks.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support ongoing compliance audits, security assessments, and continuous monitoring activities.&amp;nbsp;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot; src=&quot;https://www.jometer.com/v2/track?c=j9z3&amp;amp;a=2&quot; width=&quot;1&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At QDSS, we focus on solving complex problems that directly impact production, quality, and system performance.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you thrive in hands-on, technical environments, you’ll feel right at home here.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quest Defense Systems &amp;amp; Solutions is seeking an Electrical Engineer to support production operations&lt;/strong&gt; by troubleshooting hardware issues, resolving manufacturing challenges, and ensuring hardware builds stay on schedule. This role serves as the technical lead for production issues, partnering with manufacturing, quality, suppliers, and cross-functional engineering teams to identify root causes, implement corrective actions, and drive issues through final resolution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a hands-on engineer who can quickly assess technical problems, prioritize multiple issues, communicate effectively across teams, and take ownership from initial investigation through successful resolution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is for 1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt; shift (7a – 4p)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a 100% onsite position based in Tucson, Arizona&lt;/strong&gt;, where you&#39;ll enjoy the collaboration of working alongside your team every day. With more than 310 days of sunshine each year, stunning mountain views, and a vibrant yet relaxed lifestyle, Tucson offers an exceptional place to build both your career and your life.&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;All candidates must be US Citizens due to the nature of the work.&amp;nbsp; Clearance or the ability to obtain a clearance is strongly preferred unless otherwise stated below. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and resolve electrical hardware issues impacting production and supplier performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot complex circuit card assemblies (CCAs), electronic hardware, and electro-mechanical systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diagnose hardware failures using electronic lab equipment, including oscilloscopes, logic analyzers, function generators, and power supplies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpret electrical schematics, PCB layouts, bills of materials (BOMs), and engineering drawings to identify root causes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead production issue resolution by coordinating cross-functional teams and driving corrective actions through completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare engineering change documentation and present technical changes for review and approval.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update engineering documentation, drawings, and technical records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze defect trends and production yield data to identify opportunities for process improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with suppliers to resolve technical issues, develop Statements of Work (SOWs), and support supplier performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide day-to-day electrical engineering support for manufacturing and production environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate project status, technical risks, and resolution plans to engineering and production leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple technical issues simultaneously while balancing production priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
