&lt;li&gt;Specialized Knowledge: Exhibit expertise in areas such as manufacturability across hot structures, turbine frames, combustors, exhausts, or compressor cases, and be well-versed in aspects including manufacturing requirements, alloys, durability properties, processes, production capabilities, limitations, and MRB (Material Review Board) procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educational Foundation: Hold at least a Bachelor of Science or Bachelor of Technology degree in Mechanical or Aerospace engineering from a recognized and accredited university.&lt;/li&gt;
