&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quest Defense Systems &amp;amp; Solutions is seeking a Senior Embedded Software Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to support the design and development of mission-critical communications products for defense and aerospace applications. This is a hands-on role for someone who enjoys building reliable embedded software, working in C++, and solving technical problems across complex multi-threaded systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this position, you’ll work closely with software architects, technical leads, and cross-functional engineering teams to develop, test, and integrate embedded software solutions. The work includes object-oriented C++ development, unit testing, Python scripting, Linux-based development, networking protocols, and device driver support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to the nature of this work, all candidates must be U.S. citizens with an active Secret clearance and be willing to work onsite in Cedar Rapids, IA.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the design and development of embedded software solutions for communications products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain&amp;nbsp;unit tests&amp;nbsp;to ensure the reliability and robustness of new and legacy systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional engineering teams to ensure seamless integration with embedded systems and networking components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with system architects and technical leads to maintain and improve the overall software architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the full software development lifecycle, including design, development, testing, and deployment in a secure environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;U.S. Citizenship&amp;nbsp;with&amp;nbsp;Active Secret Clearance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with software development and integration on complex multi-threaded embedded C and C++ product software code&amp;nbsp;bases&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years&amp;nbsp;of experience with&amp;nbsp;Object-Oriented Programming&amp;nbsp;(preferably in C++)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in writing&amp;nbsp;unit tests&amp;nbsp;and ensuring code reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of&amp;nbsp;networking protocols and architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in scripting languages such as Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing or supporting&amp;nbsp;device drivers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to work onsite at Cedar Rapids (IA)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Skills and Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;TCP/IP network applications development experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;UML experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CORBA experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Linux experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with&amp;nbsp;embedded systems development for Software Defined Radios&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience working on&amp;nbsp;Department of Defense (DoD)&amp;nbsp;projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with MIL-STD-1553 and MIL-STD-188&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The QDSS Advantage:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At QDSS, our advantage is purpose-driven work, collabo

